ships/france/fr_es_crabe.htm |publisher=Navypedia | accessdate=13 April 2017 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|UIT-22||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Liuzzi|submarine}} was bombed and sunk in the [[South Atlantic]] south of the [[Cape of Good Hope]], [[Union of South Africa|South Africa]] ({{Coord|41|28|S|17|40|E}}) by [[South African Air Force]] aircraft with the loss of all 43 crew.<ref name=UIT22>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/boats/uit22.htm |title=UIT-22 |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=30 April 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-380||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC]] [[submarine]] was sunk at Toulon in an American air raid with the loss of one life.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-410||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC]] [[submarine]] was bombed and sunk at Toulon in an American air raid. }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==12 March==\n::''For the sinking of ''Sansei Maru'' on this date see the entry for [[List of shipwrecks in December 1943#8 December|8 December 1943]].\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=12 March 1944 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Kilissi||2}}\n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The [[banana boat (ship)|banana boat]] was sunk off the mouth of the [[Ebro]] by [[Royal Air Force]] aircraft. Ten crewmen were killed.<ref name=Times140344>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=Germans And A New \"Altmark Incident\" |day_of_week=Tuesday |date=14 March 1944 |page_number=3 |issue=49804 |column=E }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://sudwall.superforum.fr/t5678p25-6-sicherungs-flottille-a-gruppe |title=Kilissi |publisher=sudwall.superforum.fr |accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wrecksite.eu/wreck.aspx?150790 |title=Kilissi |publisher=www.wrecksite.eu |accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{ship