wman was lost.<ref name=seekrieg194403/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://archive.org/details/wardiarygermann551944germ/page/112 |title=German Naval War Diary |publisher=archive.org |accessdate=14 January 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Juyo Maru||2}}\n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship struck a mine and a sank in the [[Indian Ocean]] off [[Koh Chang]], Thailand.<ref name=seekrieg194403/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Lippe|1919|2}}\n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was [[torpedo]]ed by {{HMS|Sceptre|P215|6}} ({{navy|UK}}) at {{coord|64|32|N|10|38|E}} and beached in [[Nord-Tr\u00f8ndelag]], Norway. She broke in two and was declared a total loss.<ref name=seekrieg194403/><ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=1143427|shipname=Lippe |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|M 4405 Marie-Anne||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[Castle-class naval trawler|Jacquilne-class naval trawler]]/ auxiliary [[minesweeper]] was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Bay of Biscay]] off [[La Pallice]], [[Charente-Maritime]], France by aircraft of [[Coastal Command]], [[Royal Air Force]].<ref name=seekrieg194403/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|PiLB 464||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The PiLB 40 type landing craft was lost on this date.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_pilb40.htm |title=PiBL 40 type landing craft, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=3 March 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|PiLB 485||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The PiLB 40 type landing craft was lost on this date.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_pilb40.htm |title=PiBL 40 type landing craft, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=3 March 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{