-510||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of three of the 148 people on board. Survivors were rescued by {{HMS|Avon|1943|6}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=Tarifa>{{cite web |url=http://www.warsailors.com/singleships/tarifa.html |title=M/S Tarifa |publisher=Warsailors |accessdate=8 February 2012}}</ref><ref name=TarifaU510>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/3213.html |title=Tarifa |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Valera||2}}\n|flag={{flag|Panama}}\n|desc=World War II: The tanker was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Caribbean Sea]] {{convert|120|nmi|km}} north of [[Barranquilla]], Colombia ({{coord|11|30|N|76|27|W}}) by {{GS|U-518||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of one of her 35 crew. Survivors were rescued by a [[United States Coast Guard]] ship.<ref name=Valera>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/3212.html |title=Valera |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=3 April 2012}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==8 March==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=8 March 1944 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German guard ship|IV 57 Ebe||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The guard ship was sunk on this date.<ref name=\"Guard Ships of WWII, Germany\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|M 386||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The [[M-class minesweeper (Germany)|M 1940-class minesweeper]], was sunk in [[Strander Bight]] by a mine. later salvaged and repaired.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_mfp.htm |title=1940 Type Minesweepers, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=23 March 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Norco''\n|flag={{flag|United States|1912}}\n|desc=The 615-[[gross register ton]], {{convert|150.3|ft|m|1|adj=on}} [[motor vessel]] was destroyed by fire in [[Tongass Harbor]] ({{coord|54|46|30|N|130|14|30|W|name=Tongass Harbor}}) on the coast of [[Annette Island]] 