nce. The wreck was scrapped in 1945.<ref name=Jordan456-57>{{cite book |title=The world's merchant fleets, 1939 |first=Roger |last=Jordan |publisher=Chatham publishing |location=London |year=1999 |pages=456\u201357 |isbn=1 86176 023 X}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|F 513C||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The [[F-lighter|MFP-C landing craft]] was sunk on this date.<ref name=\"MFP landing craft, Germany\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_mfp.htm |title=MFP landing craft, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|F 588C||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The [[F-lighter|MFP-C landing craft]] was sunk on this date.<ref name=\"MFP landing craft, Germany\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_mfp.htm |title=MFP landing craft, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|H. D. Collier|1938|2}}\n|flag={{flag|United States|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[tank ship|tanker]] was [[torpedo]]ed, shelled and damaged in the [[Indian Ocean]] {{convert|300|nmi|km}} south south west of [[Karachi]], [[British Raj|India]] ({{coord|21|30|N|66|11|E}}) by {{ship|Japanese submarine|I-26||2}} ({{navy|Empire of Japan}}). Twelve gunners and 33 crewmen were killed. Survivors rescued by {{SS|Empire Raja||2}} ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}) and {{SS|Karagola||2}} ({{flag|British India}}). She sank on 16 March.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wrecksite.eu/wreck.aspx?37237|title=H. D. Collier Tanker 1938-1944) |publisher=Wrecksite |accessdate=13 March 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|I-O-72||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The ''Siebelgef\u00e4\u00df'' landing craft was sunk on this date.<ref name=\"navypedia.org\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_siebelgefass.htm |title=S